pinning parallel to the fabric edge is inefficient bc you need to remove the pins as you sew, if you pin perpendicular you can either sew over the pins or remove them more easily while sewing but tbh it’s a good idea to just move away from pinning in general

fwiw if your seam allowances are accurate and your fabric is notched you don’t need to pin (most of the time) bc you can just line it up
i still pin 
-at notches or start/end of seam for slippery or stretchy fabrics or lots of easing
-at notches and shoulder seam for sleeves

anyways the pinning meme is fun for showing different techniques but some of them are just inefficient and the rest are interchangeable depending on fabric type and weight (you don’t...use the same methods for vinyl and wool...) but 90% of the time you prob just shouldnt pin
